PROJECT: AI Freelance Opportunity Intelligence Platform — FRONTEND ONLY.
STACK: React + TypeScript + Vite. No backend. No API calls. Mock data only.

NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES:
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any`. Every prop, state, and mock object is typed.
- All shared types live in src/types/index.ts. Import from there — never redefine inline.
- All mock data lives in src/mockData/. Components import mock data, never hardcode arrays inside JSX.
- Reusable components only. If a UI pattern (badge, card, button) appears twice, it is a component in src/components/ui/.
- Styling: use ONE approach consistently (Tailwind CSS). No inline style objects except for dynamic values (e.g. a computed width).
- Design tokens (colors, spacing, radius, shadows) defined once in the Tailwind config / a theme file. Never hardcode hex values in components.
- Every list/table page must implement: empty state, loading state, error state.
- Do NOT install heavy UI kits (no MUI, no Ant). Allowed libs: tailwindcss, lucide-react (icons), recharts (charts), react-router-dom. Ask before adding anything else.
- Keep components under ~150 lines. Split when larger.
- When I give you a prompt, build ONLY what that prompt asks. Do not scaffold future pages early.



PROJECT: Backend for a personal freelance-intelligence tool. Python + FastAPI + SQLite.
This is a SINGLE-USER LOCAL tool for now, but write it cloud-ready (config via environment variables, no hardcoded paths or secrets).

NON-NEGOTIABLE RULES:
- Do NOT modify anything in the frontend/ folder. Backend is fully separate, in backend/.
- All secrets (Gmail credentials, etc.) come from a .env file loaded via environment variables. NEVER hardcode credentials. Add .env to .gitignore.
- The tool connects ONLY to the dedicated job-alerts inbox. It must never be able to reach a personal inbox — there is only one set of credentials and it is the dedicated inbox's.
- Email access is READ-ONLY in spirit: the tool reads emails and may mark them processed via a label/flag, but never deletes or sends email.
- Use SQLite for now via SQLAlchemy, but structure models so moving to Postgres later needs only a connection-string change.
- Keep functions small and single-purpose. Ingestion must be callable as a standalone function (so it can run manually now and on a scheduler later on a VPS).
- Type hints everywhere. No bare except. Log what happens (emails scanned, jobs added, duplicates skipped, parse failures).
- Do not build scoring, proposals, or LLM features yet. This phase is ONLY: config + database + email ingestion + a couple of API endpoints to view results.